<node CREATED="1566553055184" ID="ID_682355929" MODIFIED="1566553055184" TEXT="Dynamic SQL vs Stored Procedure. 3 (60%) 8 vote[s] Dynamic SQL and stored procedures are two of the most important components of SQL Server. In this article we will look at the advantages and disadvantages of each of them and when to use them.  If you use dynamic SQL queries in your client code you will have to update the application code " />
