<node CREATED="1566553055195" ID="ID_1776637634" MODIFIED="1566553055195" TEXT="10.4. Boyce-Codd Normal Form (BCNF) To eliminate the problems and redundancy of 3NF R.F. Boyce proposed a normal form known as Boyce-Codd normal form (BCNF). Relation R is said to be in BCNF if for every nontrivial FD: X &#226;&#8224;&#8217; Y between attributes X and Y holds in R. That means: X is super key of R. X &#226;&#8224;&#8217; Y is a trivial FD that is Y &#226;&#352;&#8218; X." />
