<node CREATED="1566553055196" ID="ID_285318811" MODIFIED="1566553055196" TEXT="Boyce-Codd Normal Form (BCNF) is one of the forms of database normalization. A database table is in BCNF if and only if there are no non-trivial functional dependencies of attributes on anything other than a superset of a candidate key. BCNF is also sometimes referred to as 3.5NF or 3.5 Normal Form." />
</node>
